While this is a remote position, we can not consider candidates that are not based in these regions. 
Nozomi Networks  is the leader of industrial cybersecurity.  Whether our clients need fast product enhancements, onsite engineering support, or rapid deployment across continents, we deliver. We accelerate digital transformation by providing exceptional network visibility, threat detection and operational insight for OT and IoT environments. 
We are looking for a DevOps engineer to expand our globally distributed team. 
In this position you will have the opportunity to develop ground-breaking technology for Industrial Cybersecurity, where Deep Packet Inspection and Artificial Intelligence are used together with Agile Methodologies to build our product. In this role, youâ€™ll have the opportunity to build, automate, maintain, and monitor our systems. Together with the rest of the team, youâ€™ll have the responsibility to make sure that our systems are up and running while performing as expected. Youâ€™ll be involved in any step of our products lifecycle acting as a reference for other engineering teams. 
Responsibilities 
Promote and implement automated solutions across application deployment, maintenance, and operational activities 
Troubleshoot issues across the entire stack, from network and OS to applications 
Performance tuning and optimisation of cloud services, including cost saving strategies 
Drive post-incident analysis according to our no-blame culture 
Participate in periodic on-call duties 
Requirements 
3+ years of professional experience as DevOps, SRE, or Cloud engineer 
Being able to understand and coding using programming languages such as Ruby, Python, and Go 
Hands-on experience on AWS 
Working experience using container orchestration tools such as k8s or ECS 
Experience defining infrastructure as code using tools such as terraform or Cloudformation 
Experience in the definition of CI/CD pipelines using technologies like Jenkins, GHA or similar 
Nice to have 
Experience with any other cloud provider (preferably GCP and Azure) 
Familiarity with centralised monitoring solutions 
Experience with Agile methodologies 
